the First and 23rd letters of the arabic alphabet.
Seperately, the first letter is pronounced as '''elif''', the second letter of the pair is pronounced as '''laam'''.
Together, the two letters are pronounced as '''el'''.
In Arabic, '''el''' is the equivalent to '''the''' in the English language, and is used to supercede the item that is being talked about. 
e.g. '''el-bayt''' which is translated to 'The house'